As a European, the fastest animal you might encounter in your daily life would likely be the European rabbit. They are known for their quick bursts of speed when they need to escape from predators. However, if you're referring to the fastest land animal, it would be the European golden hare, which can reach speeds of up to 45 km/h (28 mph). 

In terms of the fastest flying animal, it would be the European Bee-eater, which can fly at speeds of up to 35 km/h (22 mph). 

Please note that these speeds are for short bursts of movement, as these animals are not built for sustained high-speed travel.